The bard would go pull 1-4 Spirocs and then round them up into a small bundle, I would then use BoF on the group and then root one. The bard would run a small circle around the rooted one and I would root the next, and so on, until all of them were rooted fairly close together.  The bard would then use his dmg song to slowly drain the life out of them all, while I would med. Every 45 seconds to 1min or so I would re-root all the birds for safety, and he would twist in his mana song when needed.  Once the birds were at a low enough percent of life, I would use conflag to finish them off.  We had pratically no downtime, and I was always at atleast 70% mana, only having to use BoF, Root (immobalize), and a few casts of conflag.<br>
<br>
This tactic (once practiced) was very effective, mana-effecient, and safe.  <br>
<br>
Xenobicus<br>
48 Wizard -- Vazaelle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utimmahp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Timmah P</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/26/01 3:28:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: bard/wiz AE kiting</span><hr size=1> i enjoying partnering up with a bard.  the exp prolly isn't as fast as if i were solo'ing but its more fun.  plus its alot easier for the lazy wizard.  i let the bard pull and line them up,  then i snare and ae kite them. if one is left standing the bard finishes it off,  then plays mana song.  when i hit 80m, he goes off to pull.  i finish medding while he sets up the next bunch.  Besides, when you're killing raptors... there's not really any loot anyway. and the lvl 55 bard song is godly =)<br>
